6,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2395006,For Sale:  TAPCO .223/5.56 6-Position T6 Stock With Buffer Tube Black STK09161,"Willow Spring / Garner / South Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina",$ 70,"Listed On: Tuesday, April 29, 2014",Gun,no type,no type,no type,no type,"Product Description
TAPCO STK09161 BLACK AR T6 Commercial Stock Assembly, Black

When creating the INTRAFUSE® AR T6™ Stock, we didn’t want to just bring you another generic stock for your rifle.  We’ll leave that to our competition.  Instead, we made vast improvements over traditional models.  The six position stock, made of military grade composite, fits the weapon to your size and allows for a more compact fit when needed.  We’ve also reinforced the latch supports and created a thicker buttplate, giving you a more solid firing platform for acquiring your target.  Our stock is sold as a complete installation kit so you’ll not only receive the stock but also the extension tube, buffer with spring, locking plate, castle nut, and sling swivel.
TAPCO STK09161 BLACK AR T6 Commercial Stock Assembly, Black Features:
• Fits all AR15 / M16 / M4 Platforms
• 100% U.S. Made
• Includes: Commercial T6™ Stock with Composite Sling Swivel, Commercial 6 Position Receiver Extension, Buffer, Buffer Spring, AR Carbine Locking Plate, AR Carbine Castle Nut
• Lengh of Pull: 10.5"" (fully collapsed), 11.25"", 12.25"" , 13"" , 13.75"", 14.5"" (fully extended)"

There are no import markings and a ""66"" in a shield on the frame left in front of the cylinder, both suggesting 1966 manufacture.  The ""badge"" is missing from the left frame. In the past, I have bobbed the hammer of weapons like this for carry, but some may want the hammer intact.  Thus if you purchase this weapon, I will give you the info on where I get the work done, so you can if you wish.
I will include seven rounds of .32 S&W revolver cartridges so you can load it up.
$150   Cash  4% surcharge for credit card use
I', always open for a trade, what ya got?
GoldN-Guns.com"

176,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2395176,For Sale:  Czech vz. 24 Romanian Contract 8mm Mauser.,"Stafford County, Northern Virginia, Virginia",$ 285,"Listed On: Monday, December 9, 2013",Antique,no type,no type,no type,no type,"Czech vz. 24 Romanian Contract 8mm Mauser. $285. Stafford, Va.

The Czechoslovak Armaments Factory started making specially designated vz. 24s in 1938 after the German invasion. Romania was for a time part of the Axis during World War II. ""Romanian"" vz. 24s have a letter followed by an ""R"" in the serial number; for example SR 1XXX. Romanian vz. 24s ""AR"", ""BR"", ""CR""... all the way through ""YR"" represent different periods of manufacturing, no rifle with ""ZR"" has been found. The Czechs made 25,000 rifles for each period roughly totaling 625,000 Romanian vz. 24s. Romanian vz. 24's saw action in Ukraine, Bessarabia, and Stalingrad in the hands of Romanian soldiers fighting for the Axis. It was not until 1944 that Romania joined the Allies."

They are fairly basic rifles from the factory that beg for lots of user improvement. This rifle is one of the most improved that you will find while still being easily converted back to a basic SU-16 rifle if needed.
This rifle has seen light range use, about 200 rounds total fired. Cleaned well after each use.

SU-16CA rifle

I would like to sell the rifle with the M21 optic as it's zeroed for it and works very well. These are made in Israel and typically sell new for around $500. They use no batteries; the tritium element plus the light-gathering fiber optic provide all the power for the holographic reticle.

The new M6-SL is a replacement of our base model M6 rifle of old. The SL, which stands for 'stretch-lightweight', incoroprates everything a shooter needs in a quality light-weight base model rifle. Price and weight were the most important factors when developing the SL. With the M6-SL, LWRCI has brought to the market the lightest factory piston driven rifle to date.

The SL comes standard with Magpul furniture. A MOE mid-length handguard, MOE Stock, and MOE pistol grip provide excellent handling characteristics, while minimizing added weight. The SL utilizes the 'stretch' or mid-length piston system, providing a more direct recoil impulse for faster follow-up shots.

The most distinct feature of the SL is the barrel. The barrel still utilizes LWRCI's NiCorr surface conversion technology on a cold-hammer-forged barrel, but the barrel is of a smaller diameter to reduce weight.

The SL comes standard with the EXO (nickel-boron) plated one piece bolt carrier and the EXO coated enhanced fire control group. The SL also comes standard with a LWRCI Folding BUIS Rear sight and a fixed A2 front sight post.

The SL is a great addition to the LWRCI family of rifles. It provides users with an extremely lightweight rifle that incorporates our patented short-stroke piston operating system, has all of the advanced coatings that make our rifles the best in the world, and does at an entry level price.
